  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\n`truffle test --show-events` does not show events from `before` methods.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nCall a contract method that emits events.\r\nWhen called from a `before` method the events will not be shown.\r\nChange `before` to `it` and the events will show.\r\n\r\nEDIT: The events were emitted in a contract constructor but I don't think it makes a difference since the events show in one case and not another.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\n`--show-events` should always show the events.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nThe events are not shown when the test method is `before`.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Windows with WSL Ubuntu 18.04\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.0.29 (core: 5.0.29)\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v10.9.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.9.0\r\n",
